crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects suspicious PowerShell code that downloads from web sites
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This PowerShell script downloads an executable file from a remote server and saves it to the local machine. It then runs the executable with the argument "all" and saves the output to a text file. The contents of the text file are then converted to a Base64 string and sent to another remote server via HTTP requests. The script also checks for the existence of a key file in the user's public documents folder, which suggests that this script is part of a larger attack campaign.
